# Publish content guards

Before any **publish preview** or go-live step for **social media** or **webpage**, run content validation and **stop** if it fails.

## Run validation

```bash
node scripts/validate-publish.mjs <project-id-or-folder>
```

Example: `node scripts/validate-publish.mjs 0001`

**Webpage go-live** (rotate ‚Üí optimize ‚Üí validate ‚Üí checklist):

```bash
node scripts/publish-webpage.mjs <project-id> [--rotate <file> --cw|--ccw|--180] [--exif-orient]
```

**Owner manually renamed images** in the project folder ‚Üí **`sync-project-story-images.mjs` only** (HTML from disk). **Do not** run **`normalize-project-media-names.mjs`**. See [`.cursor/rules/project-images-manual-rename.mdc`](project-images-manual-rename.mdc).

When the project has **`googleReview`**, `publish-webpage.mjs` syncs the **review block** on **`index.html`** (`--no-story-review` to skip) and, when the story is live, runs **`sync-testimonials-html.mjs`** for the **Repair:** link on testimonials (`--no-testimonials` to skip).

Full limits and platform notes: [`docs/publish-content-guards.md`](../../docs/publish-content-guards.md). Webpage steps: [`docs/website-go-live.md`](../../docs/website-go-live.md).

## Publish order

1. **`validate-done-readiness.mjs`** ‚ÄĒ presentable `projectName`, `title`, `description`, `itemDetails`, `repairDetails`, skills, images; no debug/placeholder text. Human sets **`status`: `"DONE"`** only after this passes (`set-project-status.mjs --status DONE` enforces it).
2. **`publish-webpage.mjs`** ‚ÄĒ blocked unless **`status` === `"DONE"`**.
3. **`publish-social.mjs`** ‚ÄĒ blocked unless **`DONE`** + **`index.html`** + **`webpageUrl`** (story live on site first).

## Required (config + folder)

- `status` === `"DONE"` for webpage/social publish
- Presentable metadata (see `scripts/lib/project-readiness.mjs`) ‚ÄĒ not skill-list stubs, legacy gallery captions, or `T-00030` / timesheet debug text
- `title` / `description` ‚ÄĒ ‚Č§ **500** characters; **Threads** summary ‚Č§ **200** (rewritten, not truncated with `‚Ä¶`)
- `tags` ‚ÄĒ array, **1‚Äď30** strings (no `#` in JSON)
- `skills` ‚ÄĒ non-empty; only `needlework`, `electronic`, `mechanical`, `paintjob`
- **Media** ‚ÄĒ at least one project image

Also check **description + appended social hashtags** ‚Č§ **500** characters total (FB / IG).

## Tags across Facebook, Instagram, Threads

- One `tags` array in `config.json` is the source of truth for the **repair page** (all tags as chips) and gallery search (**1‚Äď30** in JSON).
- **Social (FB + IG):** at most **3** hashtags in the caption ‚ÄĒ if `config.tags` has more than three, use [`pickSocialTags()`](../../scripts/lib/social-tags.mjs) to choose the **most appropriate** three (product/character/brand over generic `plush`, `vintage`, `repair`, etc.); tie-break by original order in `config.json`. All tags still appear on the repair page.
- **Threads:** **no hashtags**; post text is `buildThreadsCaption()` ‚ÄĒ ‚Č§ **200** characters, **rewritten** from `description` via `rewriteForThreads()` (URLs stripped; no `‚Ä¶` truncation). See [`docs/publish-content-guards.md`](../../docs/publish-content-guards.md).
- **Facebook / Instagram:** same caption string ‚ÄĒ `description` + the **3** social hashtags only.
- Preview must list **social hashtags** (x/3) and **tags on story page only** when `config.tags` has more than three.

There is no shared Meta ‚Äútags‚ÄĚ API field for all three ‚ÄĒ FB/IG use `description` + picked hashtags; Threads uses the short summary only.

## Image order: social vs webpage (different on purpose)

| Channel | Order | Source |
|---------|--------|--------|
| **Webpage / HTML** (`publish-webpage.mjs`, `sync-project-story-images.mjs`) | WIP gallery: **before ‚Üí WIP-### ‚Üí after**; page hero / tile / OG: **hero ‚Üí after ‚Üí WIP ‚Üí before** | [`listStoryGalleryImageNames()`](../../scripts/lib/project-media.mjs), [`pickFeaturedImageName()`](../../scripts/lib/project-media.mjs) ‚ÄĒ **leave as-is** |
| **Social** (FB / IG / Threads carousel) | **hero ‚Üí after ‚Üí before ‚Üí WIP-###** | [`listPublishImagePaths()`](../../scripts/lib/project-media.mjs) ‚ÄĒ **social only** |

Do **not** apply social carousel order to story `index.html` or change webpage publish scripts to match social.

## Social carousel (max 10 images)

- **Cap:** **10** images per unified FB / IG / Threads carousel (`SOCIAL_CAROUSEL_MAX`).
- **Carousel order (FB / IG / Threads):** **hero ‚Üí after ‚Üí before ‚Üí WIP-###** (numeric). Implemented in [`listPublishImagePaths()`](../../scripts/lib/project-media.mjs); selection when &gt;10 keeps hero, after, before first, then WIPs.
- **When the folder has more than 10 images:** default **`--pick-images auto`** ‚ÄĒ **vision** (OpenAI, `OPENAI_API_KEY`) or **heuristic** scoring picks the best 10; falls back to **rules** (hero ‚Üí after ‚Üí before ‚Üí WIP) on failure or `--no-ai`. Preview must show **selection method**, **included/omitted**, **carousel order**, and any **notes** per omitted file.
- **Webpage** publish is **not** capped.
- **`--image after`** (etc.) = single-image post, no cap logic.

## Preview summary must include

After validation passes, the publish **preview** should show: project id, targets, `status`, URL fields, **title**, **description length** (x/500), **Threads text** (‚Č§200 rewritten, no hashtags), **social hashtags** (‚Č§3 for FB/IG, which tags + story-only tags if more in config), **included** social images (x/10), **omitted** images when truncation applies, and validation **OK** or list failures.

If validation fails, **do not** proceed to publish; report failures and ask the user to fix `config.json` or add media.

## `itemDetails` tone (About this item)

Product copy on repair pages should focus on **what the item is** ‚ÄĒ features, history, origin, materials, and how it works ‚ÄĒ not **resale value**, pricing, or ‚Äúcollector market‚ÄĚ language that can feel judgmental to owners.

- **Do:** manufacturer/era, licensed character, construction, typical mechanisms, label clues for identification.
- **Avoid:** market value, eBay sold prices, USD/AUD ranges, ‚Äúmodest/affordable/premium resale,‚ÄĚ buyer demand, sentimental vs monetary comparisons.
- **Source:** [`scripts/lib/item-details-catalog.mjs`](../../scripts/lib/item-details-catalog.mjs); refresh with [`scripts/refresh-item-details-tone.mjs`](../../scripts/refresh-item-details-tone.mjs). After bulk edits, sync live story HTML prose via `publish-webpage.mjs` or `syncProjectStoryProseHtml` (see [`project-story-prose-html.mjs`](../../scripts/lib/project-story-prose-html.mjs)).
